commit.message:
Made Table docstring visible in docs (#742)

Removed the TableBase construct in favour of the metaclass keyword argument, as
all supported python versions support it.
This results in the docstring for Table (formerly TableBase) being visible in the API docs.

commit.message:
[CI] Cleanup tox / travis configuration (#713)

- Prefer python 3.7 over 3.6 for lint
- Use official python 3.8 release
- Update setup.py for configuration matrix
- Bump black
- Use Django 3.0 rc1
- Remove useless `travis` section in tox.ini
Update changelog and bump version to 2.2.1

Fix backwards-compatibility with legacy separators in order_by clauses (#715)

* Fix backwards-compatibility with legacy separators in order_by clauses

* Replace assertWarns with assertWarnsRegex in test_utils.py

The msg keyword that was being used before does not check the
actual warning message, but rather configures the test assertion
error message.
Adjust stacklevel for DeprecationWarning, add Changelog, bump version
Do not raise the DeprecationWarning, but use warnings.warn()
Add fallback to legacy separator in Accessor
Reorder initial_sort_descending in column docstring (#708)
